stateDiagram-v2
    direction LR

    [*] --> Optimist: User submits topic<br/>(round = 0)

    Optimist --> Skeptic: Positive argument generated<br/>(messages += optimist_response)

    Skeptic --> ConditionalCheck: Challenge generated<br/>(messages += skeptic_response,<br/>round += 1)

    ConditionalCheck --> Optimist: if (round < 3)<br/>Continue debate
    ConditionalCheck --> Moderator: if (round >= 3)<br/>End debate

    Moderator --> [*]: Summary generated<br/>(debate complete)

    note right of ConditionalCheck
        Conditional Edge Logic:
        state.round < 3 ? "optimist" : "moderator"

        This replaces traditional for-loops
        with declarative flow control
    end note

    note left of Optimist
        Agent Node: optimistNode()
        - Reads state.messages
        - Invokes Groq LLM
        - Returns { messages: [response] }
    end note

    note left of Skeptic
        Agent Node: skepticNode()
        - Reads state.messages
        - Invokes Groq LLM
        - Returns {
            messages: [response],
            round: state.round + 1
          }
    end note
